<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>So I=E2=80=99m sure you have a question now. <em><strong>Why use a craft=
ing calculator at all?</strong></em></p>
<p>If I=E2=80=99m going to make up a price anyway, why go through the hassl=
e of doing all that <em>freaking math?!</em></p>
<p>The answer is simple: you have to have a handle on what it costs you, bo=
th time and supplies-wise to be able to make up your price. You also have t=
o have a handle on market rates, what people pay, and what your bottom line=
 will be.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h3><strong>When I first started selling stuff, I didn=E2=80=99t bother wit=
h a handmade jewelry price calculator.</strong></h3>
