<p>Here=E2=80=99s what happened:</p>
<p>I figured I can make a cheap pair of earrings. It cost me roughly 50 cen=
ts in quantity supplies and took me an hour to make ten pairs.</p>
<p>So if I sold it for $5 I was cutting a good profit, right?</p>
<p>I nearly went nuts with this. I wasn=E2=80=99t taking into account the c=
ost of trial and error, the fact that I was investing in supplies, not all =
of which gets used. This is why I now markup the cost <em>and </em>charge a=
 bigger hourly rate.</p>
<p>I also didn=E2=80=99t calculate running time and costs:</p>
